<main>
  {{#if paymentIntentId}}
    {{#if isSuccess}}
      <div class="mt-40 text-center text-success">
        <h1><i class="far fa-check-circle"></i> Order received!</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-40 text-center">
        <p>Total charged: <strong>$<span class="amount" data-amount="{{amount}}"></span></strong></p>
        <p class="text-muted mt-20">Payment Intent ID:</p>
        <p><code>{{paymentIntentId}}</code></p>
        <p class="text-muted mt-20">Status: <code>{{status}}</code></p>
      </div>

      {{!-- The teaching moment: this page did NOT fulfill the order. --}}
      <div class="card box-shadow mt-40 key-note">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5><i class="fas fa-bolt text-warning"></i> Fulfillment came from the event, not this page</h5>
          <p>
            You're here because Stripe redirected your browser after payment.
            But the kitchen was told to cook — and the restaurant and driver get
            paid — by a server-side <code>payment_intent.succeeded</code> event,
            <strong>not</strong> by this redirect.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-0">
            A browser can close, lose signal, or be faked. The event from Stripe
            is the trustworthy "money moved" signal. That's why
            <strong>Stripe is the system of record and fulfillment runs off
            events.</strong> Check your server terminal for
            <code>FULFILL ORDER …</code>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center mt-40"><a href="/" class="btn btn-outline-primary">Back to menu</a></p>
    {{else}}
      <div class="mt-40 text-center text-warning">
        <h1><i class="far fa-clock"></i> Payment not completed</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-40 text-center">
        <p>This payment is not in a completed state.</p>
        <p class="text-muted mt-20">Current status: <code>{{status}}</code></p>
        <p class="text-muted mt-20">Payment Intent ID:</p>
        <p><code>{{paymentIntentId}}</code></p>
        <p class="mt-40"><a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Back to menu</a></p>
      </div>
    {{/if}}
  {{else}}
    <div class="mt-40 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-secondary">No payment to display</h1>
      <p class="text-muted mt-20">It looks like you reached this page without completing an order.</p>
      <p class="mt-40"><a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Back to menu</a></p>
    </div>
  {{/if}}
</main>
